{# Jinja2 template used by bin/generate-security-advisory -#}
[[!meta date="{{date}}"]]
[[!meta title="Known security vulnerabilities in Tails {{previous_version}}"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

Tails {{version}} fixes known security
vulnerabilities in {{previous_version}}. You should upgrade as soon as possible.

If you are interested in learning more about the security vulnerabilities fixed
in this release, you can refer to:

- The release notes of *Tor Browser* and other applications linked from
  the [[release notes of Tails {{version}}|news/version_{{tag}}]].

- The list of recent [Debian security
  advisories](https://www.debian.org/security/) published since Tails
  {{previous_version}}.
